Third-party protocols (interoperated with, not included)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
rome-bridge-api is an off-chain HTTP orchestrator. It composes public
cross-chain transport and on-chain bridge primitives via their public
interfaces; it does NOT contain, fork, or redistribute the source of any of
these protocols, each of which remains the property of its authors and is
governed by its own license and trademarks:

  Circle CCTP (Cross-Chain Transfer Protocol) · Wormhole.

Chain metadata (chainIds, contract addresses, gas mints, bridge wiring) is
sourced from the public rome-protocol/rome-registry.

